title: WNBA All-Star: Live updates, results, analysis from Friday
description: Caitlin Clark is out, but the party in Indianapolis is on in Friday's 3-point contest and skills challenge.

title: Ex-NFLPA boss' strip club expenses face scrutiny
description: Former NFL Players Association leader Lloyd Howell Jr. resigned after an outside investigator hired by the union received documents this week showing he charged the union for two visits to strip clubs.
author: Don Van Natta Jr. and Kalyn Kahler

title: Commanding Scheffler leads from Fitzpatrick at rain-hit Open
description: Scottie Scheffler battles the worst of the torrential downpours to claim a one-shot lead over Matt Fitzpatrick at the Open Championship's halfway point.

title: Arsenal complete £48.5m signing of Madueke from Chelsea
description: Arsenal complete the signing of England winger Noni Madueke from Chelsea for an initial fee of £48.5m.

title: Man Utd agree deal to sign Mbeumo
description: Manchester United have reached an agreement with Brentford to sign Bryan Mbeumo.

title: Wiegman: England's dramatic Euros win 'hardest game I've ever watched'
description: Sarina Wiegman has called England's dramatic penalty shoot-out win against Sweden at Euro 2025 "the hardest game I've ever watched".

title: Ionescu wins 3-point contest, Cloud claims skills competition in New York Liberty sweep
author: DOUG FEINBERG

title: Terry Rozier subject of 30 bets placed in 46 minutes for March 2023 game, according to federal investigation: Report
description: While the NBA cleared Rozier in its probe of the unusual betting activity, the federal investgation remains open.
